description.p:
means for receiving/transmitting each of (i) linearly polarized signals, and (ii) at least one of horizontally and vertically polarized signals;


means for simultaneously receiving/transmitting at least two of: (i) horizontally polarized signals; (ii) vertically polarized signals; and (iii) circularly polarized signals;


a reflective member communicatively associated with first and second lenses; and


wherein each of said first and second lenses are bifocal lenses.
